<p>The <strong>Department of Materials Engineering</strong> (DEMAR) started its activities in 1978 with the <strong>Niobium Project</strong> (check out <a href="/Demar/en/historico/">our story</a>) and since 2006 has joined the  Lorena School of Engineering (<a href="https://site.eel.usp.br/">EEL</a>), one of the Teaching and Research Units of the largest university in Brazil, the <strong>University of São Paulo</strong> (<a href="https://www5.usp.br/">USP</a>).</p>

<p><strong>DEMAR</strong> coordinates and ministers the specific disciplines of undergraduate courses in <strong>Engineering Physics</strong> and <strong>Materials Engineering</strong>, as well as disciplines related to the materials area of ​​the <strong>EEL/USP</strong> Basic Cycle. The  department’s faculty also teach courses and dissertations in the <strong>Graduate Program in Materials Engineering</strong> (master’s and doctorate) and in the <strong>Graduate Program in Educational Sciences Projects</strong> (professional master’s degree).</p>

<p><strong>DEMAR</strong>’s facilities are located in <strong>Area II of EEL/USP</strong>, in the city of Lorena, 200km from São Paulo (<a href="/Demar/en/contact/">access route</a>).</p>

